    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Syzygium aromaticum are the result of its rich composition of bioactive compounds. The antimicrobial property of this plant is attributed to the presence of volatile oils, specifically eugenol, which exhibits broad-spectrum activity against various pathogens. The antioxidant properties of Syzygium aromaticum are due to the flavonoid content, including quercetin and kaempferol, which can scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The anti-inflammatory property of this plant is also significant, as it has been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes, such as COX-2 and lipoxygenase, thereby reducing inflammation. Additionally, the antifungal and analgesic properties of Syzygium aromaticum are attributed to the sesquiterpene and phenolic compounds present in its essential oil, which exhibit antifungal activity against various fungi and provide pain relief through the inhibition of pain mediators.",
